1. Architecture & Scope
✓ DECISION: The prototype is a governed MDM front-end, not a full-stack application.
The prototype demonstrates all UI workflows, data structures, and governance logic. It does not implement a real backend, authentication, or live API connections. All data is seeded and persisted locally.
✓ DECISION: The prototype scope covers the admin-facing Registry application only.
Specifically: Course Catalog, Credentials, Schema Manager, Bulk Upload, Approval Workflow, Edit Modals, CSV Template Generation, and the Analytics panel stub. Course Patterns and the full Course Sherpa student interface are partially scaffolded but not fully built out.
✓ DECISION: The Registry enriches MDM records with Ed-Fi and warehouse data at query time.
It does not copy or store Ed-Fi or IDOE Data Warehouse data in the MDM database. Those are read-only enrichment sources.
✓ DECISION: Cohort-locking protects students whose plans were built against a prior year's data.
A student's plan evaluated against the v2025 API continues to use v2025 rules regardless of subsequent changes to the live catalog.
✓ DECISION: The API supports a rolling 4-year window of simultaneously live versions.
Deprecated versions remain accessible for 18 months after a new release is published.

2. Technology Decisions
✓ DECISION: Prototype built as a single HTML file, not a React or Angular project.
Rationale: The CIO is building from a Chromebook without a local development environment. A single file can be edited directly in GitHub and deployed instantly via Cloudflare Pages. The dev team uses this as a visual and behavioral specification, not as code to extend directly.
✓ DECISION: Deployed to Cloudflare Pages (not Cloudflare Workers).
Cloudflare Pages is designed for static/SPA deployments. No build step is required — the HTML file is served as-is. The deployment URL is the CIO's personal zvillekellers.workers.dev subdomain.
✓ DECISION: localStorage used for prototype persistence.
Three storage keys are used:

ipr_schemas_v1 — Schema Manager field definitions for both libraries
ipr_apqueue_v1 — Approval queue state
ipr_courses_v1 — Course Catalog records
ipr_creds_v1 — Credentials records

Storage keys are versioned so schema changes to the data model automatically invalidate stale stored data. A Reset to Defaults button in the Schema Manager wipes all localStorage and restores seed data.
✓ DECISION: Production stack is Angular or Blazor + Azure Functions (.NET) + Azure SQL.
The IDOE dev team uses Blazor/C#. The prototype is React-pattern HTML/JS and serves as a visual spec — dev team rewrites in their stack. The data structures, business rules, and workflow logic documented here carry over directly.

