5. Data Persistence (Prototype)
✓ DECISION: All data mutations save to localStorage automatically — no explicit save button.
Every action that changes state (submit, approve, reject, withdraw, bulk import) calls persistSave() immediately.
✓ DECISION: Reset to Defaults wipes all four localStorage keys and restores seed data.
This is available as a red-outlined button in the Schema Manager header. It confirms before executing. Useful at the start of a new test run.
✓ DECISION: Seed data is defined as *Default arrays in JavaScript.
ccCoursesDefault, crCredsDefault, smSchemasDefault, apQueueDefault — these are deep-copied on reset, not mutated directly.
✓ DECISION: In production, localStorage is replaced by Azure SQL.
The data structures in the prototype map directly to database tables. No architectural changes to the business logic are required — only the storage layer changes.

6. Course Catalog
✓ DECISION: The Course Catalog is a live data-driven list, not a static table.
Records are stored in ccCourses (persisted to ipr_courses_v1). The table renders from this array on every navigation event and search/filter change.
✓ DECISION: Filter pills use the following subject categories:

All Active
English Language & Literature
Mathematics
Science
Social Sciences & History
CTE
New This Year

Filter logic matches on the full category string and common abbreviations (e.g. "ELA", "english", "literature" all match "English Language & Literature").
✓ DECISION: "New This Year" filter shows any course with isNew: true.
This flag is set on all bulk-uploaded courses and manually added courses. It is not cleared on approval — it persists for the cohort year.
✓ DECISION: Search filters live across course code, course name, and category.
The footer updates in real time: "Showing 1–15 of 23 records matching 'biology'".
✓ DECISION: Pagination is 15 rows per page.
✓ DECISION: Courses imported via bulk upload arrive with status: 'pending' and isNew: true.
They are visible in the Course Catalog immediately after import and searchable. They do not appear as "Active" until a Curriculum Director approves them in Pending Approvals.
✓ DECISION: Seed data includes 8 demo courses.
These represent a realistic cross-section of ELA, Math, Science, Social Studies, and CTE courses with real Indiana course codes.

