13. Analytics Panel
✓ DECISION: Panel is titled "Trends & Utilization" (not "Enrollment & Utilization").
✓ DECISION: The Indiana county choropleth map is a placeholder in the prototype.
Production requires real data binding so the map reclassifies dynamically when a different course or credential is selected. The SRS identifies this as a known gap requiring real data pipeline integration.
✓ DECISION: KPI tiles and trend bars in the prototype use realistic but static seed data.
Production replaces these with live queries against the IDOE Data Warehouse.

14. Course Sherpa (Student App)
✓ DECISION: Course Sherpa is a sessionless student diploma planning tool, accessible via Apps → Course Sherpa.
No student login required. Plans are saved via email-code persistence (not implemented in prototype).
✓ DECISION: The AI Course Assistant uses a BYOK (Bring Your Own Key) model.
The student or counselor enters their own Anthropic API key. Key is stored in browser memory only — never sent to IDOE servers. Browser calls api.anthropic.com directly using the user's key.
✓ DECISION: Required UI disclosure before key entry:
"Your API key will be visible in browser network traffic. Set a spending limit on your Anthropic account before using this feature."
✓ DECISION: FERPA compliance is maintained because IDOE servers are not in the transcript data chain.
Browser reads the uploaded transcript file and sends it directly to Anthropic. IDOE never receives, processes, or stores transcript content.
✓ DECISION: The full Course Sherpa student interface (four-year planner, diploma progress bars, AI counselor modal) is scaffolded but not fully built in the current prototype.
It is the next major build milestone.

