16. Out of Scope for Prototype
The following are architecturally defined and anticipated but not built in the current prototype:

Course Sherpa full student interface — four-year planner, diploma progress bars, seal tracker, AI counselor modal
Credential bulk upload — scaffolded as a button; workflow identical to Course Catalog bulk upload
Course Patterns panel — scaffolded with static data; lifecycle states (Quarantine → Emerging → Established → Shifting → Archived), CUSUM monitoring, and DGC review workflow not implemented
Modal Editor — the governed tool for configuring which fields appear in edit modals and their layout. Scaffolded in nav; not built. Edit modals currently use hardcoded field sets.
AI Staging Area — scaffolded with static data; SCED code suggestions, diploma category suggestions, and delta narratives not wired to real AI
Publication panel — scaffolded with static data; Golden Snapshot promotion, diff endpoint, and AI-drafted release notes not implemented
Schema Manager for Course Patterns — only Course Catalog and Credentials schemas are built
Sherpa API context bundle endpoint — architecturally defined; not wired to a live backend
Server-side BYOK proxy — for institutional users wanting AI assistance at scale
CTDL/JSON-LD diploma credential definition — formal machine-readable diploma rules
County SVG map dynamic reclassification — Trends & Utilization map needs real data binding
Authentication & role management — prototype uses a role simulator dropdown; production requires real identity management (Azure AD or Indiana SSO)
Ed-Fi ODS API integration — prototype uses static enrollment data; production reads live from Indiana centralized ODS
IDOE Data Warehouse integration — prototype uses static trend data; production reads from the warehouse


